President Joe Biden has issued an order to fly the flag of the United States at half-staff in remembrance of the one million American lives lost to COVID-19. He acknowledges the irreplaceable loss and the impact it has had on families, communities, and the nation. He emphasizes the importance of remaining vigilant against the pandemic and doing everything possible to save lives. The flag will be flown at half-staff at the White House, public buildings, military posts, naval stations, and naval vessels until May 16, 2022. The order also extends to United States embassies, consular offices, and military facilities abroad. President Biden concludes by expressing his commitment to overcoming this crisis together as the United States of America.